---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro'

const bookingHref = 'https://cal.com/builtbywin/20-min-ai-sprint-fit-call'
---

<BlogLayout
  title="work with me"
  description="A four-call AI app sprint for small-business owners whose work is spread across Shopify, Google Sheets, Drive, and email"
  pathSegments={[{ name: 'work-with-me', href: null }]}
  backHref="/ston"
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>work-with-me/</h1>
    <p class="page-description">turn the tools you already use into a custom app</p>
  </header>

  <section class="hero">
    <h2>turn the tools you already use into an app for your business</h2>
    <p>
      if your business runs on shopify, google sheets, drive, email, or tools that do not quite
      work together, i will help you build the missing piece—and teach you how to keep improving it
      with ai. no coding background required.
    </p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={bookingHref} data-work-with-me-cta="hero">
      book a free 20-minute call →
    </a>
    <p class="availability">4 calls · $1,500 · three founding-client spots · mac required</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what you will get</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>an ai coding and development environment configured on your mac</li>
      <li>the foundation of a new app deployed online after our first call</li>
      <li>one painful business workflow connected to the tools you already use</li>
      <li>a useful feature working end to end for your customers or staff</li>
      <li>a repeatable workflow for continuing to improve the app yourself</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what to expect</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>call 1—build the foundation:</strong> set up your ai coding tools and developer
        environment, create the new app, and deploy it to the web. we are not fixing every business
        integration yet—you leave with a working foundation you can begin prompting and changing.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>calls 2–4—connect and ship:</strong> choose one painful workflow and get the
        solution working end to end—for example, by connecting the shopify store, spreadsheet,
        files, or other tools involved.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>between calls:</strong> keep building on your own and bring back anything blocked,
        broken, or ready for review. add another call whenever you need more help getting unstuck.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>founding-client requirements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>you use a mac that you can install developer tools on</li>
      <li>you already run a business and have a specific recurring problem to solve</li>
      <li>you can access the shopify account, spreadsheet, files, or tools we need to connect</li>
      <li>you are willing to work hands-on during and between calls</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="muted">
      no coding experience is required. this is not for a vague startup idea or fully outsourced
      development—we will build around a real workflow in your existing business.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>why me</h2>
    <p>
      i am a <a href="/ston/resume">software engineer with almost a decade of experience</a>. i
      have built production-quality apps for myself and for big tech companies.
    </p>
    <p>
      through <a href="https://zerostack.builtby.win/">zero stack</a>, i have taught other
      business owners how to build with ai. their projects include
      <a href="https://cfwproductions.com/">cfw productions</a>,
      <a href="https://flash.handlworks.com/">flash</a>, and
      <a href="https://import-bonds.reddata.io/">import bonds</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      i am a problem solver and a builder, so i will help you build exactly what you need as
      cheaply as possible—and teach you how to be your own developer. you do not need a new bill.
      you need a new skill.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>what happens next</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        book a free call and tell me what tools run your business, what still happens manually, and
        where your customers or staff get stuck.
        <details>
          <summary>some ideas</summary>
          <ul>
            <li>a shopify dashboard for orders that need attention</li>
            <li>a client portal powered by google sheets or drive</li>
            <li>customer intake connected to your existing workflow</li>
            <li>an internal tool that replaces repetitive copy-paste work</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
      </li>
      <li>we discuss what would be useful for your business and whether the sprint is a good fit</li>
      <li>if it is, i send the scope, call schedule, and payment link</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="final-cta">
    <h2>what should your tools do that they do not do now?</h2>
    <p>tell me what is still manual. we will find the smallest useful app to build around it.</p>
    <a class="primary-cta" href={bookingHref} data-work-with-me-cta="footer">
      book a free 20-minute call →
    </a>
  </section>
</BlogLayout>
<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-work-with-me-cta]').forEach((link) => {
    link.addEventListener('click', () => {
      window.posthog?.capture('work_with_me_cta_clicked', {
        cta_location: link.getAttribute('data-work-with-me-cta'),
        offer: 'ai_app_sprint',
        price_usd: 1500,
      })
    })
  })
</script>

<style>
  .page-header,
  .hero,
  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-header h1,
  h2 {
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability,
  .muted {
    color: var(--color-term-fg-muted);
  }

  .page-description,
  .availability {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  p,
  li {
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul,
  ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: disc;
  }

  ol {
    list-style: decimal;
  }

  li + li {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  details {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  details ul {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  summary {
    width: fit-content;
    color: var(--color-term-link);
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-term-link);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .primary-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-term-bg);
    background: var(--color-term-dir);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-term-dir);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .primary-cta:hover,
  .primary-cta:focus-visible {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--color-term-dir);
  }

  .muted {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .final-cta {
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-term-bg-lighter);
  }

  @media (max-width: 40rem) {
    .primary-cta {
      display: block;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
